<TITLE> Fire at Italy steel plant kills one, injures seven </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Turin, Italy, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A fire at a steel factory in the Italian city of Turin killed one worker and injured seven early on Thursday, police said. The dead and injured were night-shift workers at the ThyssenKrupp plant. Police said the fire broke out at about 1:10 a.m. (0010 GMT). Six of the injured suffered serious burns
